[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURndjl6WDd3RRAB","review_link":"https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURndjl6WDd3RRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xd74f133bfb0dcd43!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgMDgv9zX7wE%7CCgwIhcaIvgYQsIXspAM%7C?hl=en-GB","name":"Share Share","reviewer_id":"107557588153745055831","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107557588153745055831?hl=en-GB","rating":5,"review_text":"The First Garden Night Market, also known as Pasar Malam Taman Pertama, is a vibrant and bustling open-air market in Ipoh, Perak. Held exclusively on Fridays from 5:30 PM to 10:30 PM, it stands as one of the largest night markets in the area, featuring approximately 200 stalls.

Visitors can indulge in a diverse array of local delicacies, including popular dishes like assam laksa, fried carrot cake, popiah (Chinese spring rolls), char kueh (fried rice cake), and orh luak (fried oyster omelette). The market also offers a variety of beverages, fresh fruits, vegetables, clothing, and daily essentials, making it a one-stop destination for both dining and shopping.

The atmosphere is lively, with the market coming alive in the cooler evening hours. However, it tends to get crowded after dark, so arriving earlier might provide a more comfortable experience.

Reached the place at 5.30pm and many stalls were yet to arrive to start setting up their respective stalls...
The walkway was active with many motorcycles that drove thru and flow the market... quite dangerous...
At about 6.35pm most of the stalls were in full swing and busy with their business... yet still quite a few stalls not operating... can see empty space between stalls....
This Pasar Malam was not a very big one as compared with the few that visited before...
